Data for a single person

ds<- dsL %>% dplyr::filter(id==1,year %in% c(2000:2011)) %>% dplyr::select(id,year,attend) 
print(ds)
   id year attend
1   1 2000      1
2   1 2001      6
3   1 2002      2
4   1 2003      1
5   1 2004      1
6   1 2005      1
7   1 2006      1

9   1 2008      1

add a straight line to represent possible predition line, in this case a straight line

linear<- predict(lm(attend ~ year, ds))
ds<- ds %>% dplyr::mutate(linear=linear)
print(ds)
   id year attend linear
1   1 2000      1 2.5000
2   1 2001      6 2.3182
3   1 2002      2 2.1364
4   1 2003      1 1.9545
5   1 2004      1 1.7727
6   1 2005      1 1.5909
7   1 2006      1 1.4091
8   1 2007      1 1.2273
9   1 2008      1 1.0455
10  1 2009      1 0.8636
11  1 2010      1 0.6818
12  1 2011      1 0.5000
p<-p+ geom_line(aes(y=linear),color="red", size=.5)
p

Or adding the curvarture the quadratic term

quadratic<- predict(lm(attend ~ year + I(year^2),ds))
ds<- ds %>% mutate(quadratic=quadratic)
print(ds)
   id year attend linear quadratic
1   1 2000      1 2.5000    3.0769
2   1 2001      6 2.3182    2.5804
3   1 2002      2 2.1364    2.1469
4   1 2003      1 1.9545    1.7762
5   1 2004      1 1.7727    1.4685
6   1 2005      1 1.5909    1.2238
7   1 2006      1 1.4091    1.0420
8   1 2007      1 1.2273    0.9231
9   1 2008      1 1.0455    0.8671
10  1 2009      1 0.8636    0.8741
11  1 2010      1 0.6818    0.9441
12  1 2011      1 0.5000    1.0769
p<-p+ geom_line(aes(y=quadratic),color="blue", size=.5)
 p

or the cubic term

cubic<- predict(lm(attend ~ year + I(year^2) + I(year^3),ds))
ds<- ds %>% mutate( cubic=cubic)
print(ds)
   id year attend linear quadratic  cubic
